title: Fernhill B2 — keyless tool gates (R3 spelling): crowbar → crate → opener → tin
story: fernhill
description: Two chained tool gates in the current R3 keyless `with` spelling —
  the nailed crate needs the crowbar (fetched from the dark cellar, so the A4
  lamp chain is exercised for real), and the kipper tin needs the tin opener
  found inside the crate. Each gate is asserted failing WITHOUT its tool first.
